SPARKLE SAMMY led the field into the first turn, continued to dictate the pace down the back straight, was headed outside by the winner turning for home, fought on stubbornly until deep stretch and faded late losing placings just before the wire. COURTINGCOURTNEY was allowed to settle near the rear entering the first turn, trailed in the two path at the half, was asked for run three eighths from home, offered little run and passed a tiring rival in the final furlong. PHIL IN ECHO stalked at the rear just off the fence into the first turn, travelled inside down the backside, was scrubbed on for more run at the three furlong pole and gave way entering the stretch.

ROSES ARE FREE settled near the rear three deep between rivals down the backside, was asked to keep pace with others with three eighths remaining and lost touch with the field through the turn.

SECRET RESERVE was up close to the leaders outside rivals going four to five wide, dropped back and faded. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUPER DORMY broke sharp to be in front at the start, soon after relaxed to have a good position rating kindly inside behind the leaders, waited comfortably throughout the turn, was headstrong straightening out for the drive when looking for a clear path, finally found a seam at the three sixteenth pole, burst on by splitting runners and won going away at the wire. LUCKY SCORE stalked near the rear on the rail in the early stages, saved all the ground inside on the turn, rallied on the fence in upper stretch , angled off the tiring leaders at the eighth pole and split foes late getting for the second money. VOODOO ZIP settled in the middle of the pack on the fence with a half remaining, sat behind the winner at the quarter marker looking for room, found a clear lane four deep at the furlong pole and finished strong just missing out on the runner up finish at the line. STRIKER prompted the pace outside down the backside and throughout the turn, was headed running between rivals in the two path at the eighth pole and faded in deep stretch to hold for a minor role. ROARING FORTIES took a slim lead under a snug hold travelling up front through the turn, was collared outside by multiple runners at the furlong marker and yielded on the fence in the late stages of the race. COINAGE trailed the field at the half, continued to be last turning for home, angled out to the seven path for the drive and offered late energy to finish up strongly not being beaten all that much for the runner up share in the end. FULL SCREEN stalked inside near the back of the field in the beginning, angled outside three wide on the turn, shifted in for the stretch drive on the rail and could not get involved running to the finish. IRONSTONE travelled outside of rivals in midfield three wide at the three furlong pole, shifted out starting a rally in the seven path at the top of the lane and made little impression outside to the wire. SILENT RUNNER tracked in the second flight outside three deep on the turn, was ridden in the five path at the quarter pole to keep pace between foes and gave way in mid stretch. SHEKKY SHEBAZ tracked the engaging duo with runners on either side throughout the turn, bid four wide in upper stretch and retreated between horses at the furlong marker.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TREASON stalked the leading pair from outside into the first turn going four to five wide on that bend, continued just off those two into the far turn, took over the lead at the five-sixteenths, was clear turning for home, held at bay the challenge of CARROTHERS, who was caught outside foes in the second flight going five wide on the first turn, raced just off the leading trio up the backstretch into the far turn, urged along about the five-sixteenths, came into upper stretch with aim on the winner, drifted about and could make no headway. TYSON broke outwardly just a bit, settled in behind the leaders in the second flight racing two to four wide throughout, kept on in the lane to secure show honors. ARTIE'S STORM was in a bit tight between runners just after the break, settled in the back half of the field racing near inside, began to pick it up two to three wide on the far turn, rallied in the stretch to get up for fourth. WOLFIE'S DYNAGHOST pressed the early pace from outside in about the three to four path, applied more pressure up the backstretch at the five-and-one-half taking a narrow lead, continued two to three deep on the far turn but was overtaken late on that bend, lacked the needed late kick. CONGLOMERATE settled off the pace shifting in three to four wide into the first turn, swung eight deep turning for home, gained mildly. WAR BOMBER (IRE) got away alertly and went straight to the front, dictated the early terms racing just off the rail, was pressured early up the backstretch and continued to be prominent inside, gave way in the stretch. RONDURE settled off the pace caught four to five wide early, made a mild advance on the far turn still four to five deep, never reached serious contention and flattened out in the lane. AVOMAN tracked from inside up close to the leaders, steadily weakened past the quarter pole. BRINGER OF RAIN settled mid-pack off the rail, raced two to four wide throughout and failed to rally. LUCKMAN trailed the field early and was never near enough to threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIMCOE had a good position on the rail watching the front two runners engage down the backstretch, waited inside on the far turn, bullied his way through in the two path at the top of the lane, opened up at the eighth pole and held safe crossing the finish line. WICKENHEISER was taken back to be near the rear soon after the start, settled in the middle of the pack on the rail at the half, waited inside midway on the far turn, had no path in upper stretch, finally found a seam at the eighth pole and finished strongly to garner the runner up position at the wire. RED LINE OVERDRIVE took command from the onset, set the fractions on the first turn, dictated the pace down the back straight, continued to battle on the front taken the field into the stretch drive, was collared by the winner a furlong out and faded the last sixteenth to hold for a small share of the prize. HALL OF DREAMS trailed the field with a half left to run, burst between runners splitting foes midpoint on the turn, loomed boldly seven wide at the top of the stretch and stalled in the final furlong. MO TOURIST was pushed inwards at the break, settled in midpack two wide at the half, had no room from the quarter pole to the top of the stretch, angled outwards eight wide at the eighth pole and finished evenly to the wire. MAD MOCHA tracked just outside in the two path watching the top pair down the backside, was ridden to keep when the pace quicken midpoint on the final turn and tired between runners in upper stretch. CURLIN'S GHOST was in tight quarters soon after the break, clipping inside rivals heels, stumbled, recovered to be with the pack down the backstretch, put in a mild rally into the far turn and stopped at the five sixteenths pole.
